arStrings.szText: On my way here, I passed the old orphanage in the bazaar. I grew up in one just like it. No family by blood, but dozens of brothers, sisters...
It was filled with children like them when we arrived with the Mother. A few of them came out to fight us. One was barely ten years old, holding a plank of wood...
Somber. Heavy. Trailing off in memory.
I told myself I was sparing him from the horror to come... but standing here, I imagine how he felt. Knowing I canâ€™t win. But knowing I have to fight.
Coming to the point. Somber. Heavy.
